{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #233: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $d_n=p_{n+1}-p_n$, where $p_n$ is the $n$th prime. Prove that\\[\\sum_{1\\leq n\\leq N}d_n^2 \\ll N(\\log N)^2.\\] Current best: Cramer \\cite{Cr36} proved an upper bound of $O(N(\\log N)^4)$ conditional on the Riemann hypothesis. Selberg \\cite{Se43} improved this slightly (still assuming the Riemann hypothesis) to\\[\\sum_{1\\leq n\\leq N}\\frac{d_n^2}{n}\\ll (\\log N)^4.\\]The prime number theorem immediately implies a lower bound of\\[\\sum_{1\\leq n\\leq N}d_n^2\\gg N(\\log N)^2.\\]The values of the sum are listed at A074741 on the OEIS. Prize: no. OEIS: A074741. Tags: number theory, primes.","id":"vf_150f4fce8be33076","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos233.erdos_233.variants.lower_bound https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos233.erdos_233.variants.lower_bound.","id":"vf_b54252b73f70fd9b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/233.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_150f4fce8be33076","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:233","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_b54252b73f70fd9b","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:233","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_b54252b73f70fd9b","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d83